## Scope

This slice pulls storage/JSON in EARLY — before any of the feature parts — so that every later part can fill its `$defs` and serialize against a single, already-validated envelope. It implements the four [Core] storage directives of Part I (§I.1–§I.4) over the `OpticalConstructorProject` aggregate that slice 002 defined: canonical `System.Text.Json` + FSharp.SystemTextJson round-trip, the published JSON Schema with validate-on-load via JsonSchema.Net, `.ocproj` file read/write through the single project-open seam, and `.binz` sidecars for derived/bulk artefacts only. Because `ProjectJson` is reflection-based (FSharp.SystemTextJson), new aggregate fields auto-serialize as later slices extend the record; each later slice extends the schema, not the serializer.

This slice depends on slice 002 (the aggregate plus the nine `$defs` anchor names). The aggregate currently holds the beam tree + systems; later slices extend it (materials → slice 004, sources → slice 007, chart settings → slice 012). The `StorageError` DU in `Errors.fs` is the sole error channel for storage — every IO function returns a `Result<_, StorageError>`, never throwing.

## Requirements

### R-1. §I.1 [Core] — Canonical JSON serialization of the project root

`OpticalConstructor.Storage.fsproj` MUST provide a module `OpticalConstructor.Storage.ProjectJson` exposing `serializeProject : OpticalConstructorProject -> Result<string, StorageError>` and `deserializeProject : string -> Result<OpticalConstructorProject, StorageError>` over the Part A root aggregate `OpticalConstructorProject` (§A.7). Serialization MUST use **System.Text.Json with FSharp.SystemTextJson** (the package Part A admits) configured with `JsonFSharpOptions` so that F# records, discriminated unions (`ConstructorElement`, `BeamBranch`, `Substrate`, `Thickness`, `WaveLength`), and `option` values round-trip idiomatically; it MUST NOT use Newtonsoft or FsPickler for this path (binding rule 4).

Reuse before invention: do NOT hand-roll a JSON writer — the single primitive to reach for is `System.Text.Json.JsonSerializer.Serialize/Deserialize` with the `FSharp.SystemTextJson` converter registered once in a shared `JsonSerializerOptions` value. The serializer MUST write the domain model's canonical SI fields verbatim: `Thickness of double<meter>` (`Media.fs:12`) and `WaveLength.value : double<meter>` (`Fields.fs:284`) are emitted as their stored meter values; the human-facing unit travels only in the `unitOfMeasure` field (§A.7 `unitOfMeasure` `$def`). No unit conversion, rounding, or canonicalization of physical magnitudes occurs in this module.

`StorageError` MUST be a net-new DU in `OpticalConstructor.Storage.Errors` with cases at minimum `JsonParseError of string`, `SchemaValidationError of string list`, `SchemaMissing`, `FileIoError of exn`, `BinzError of exn`, and `SidecarMissing of string`. It MUST NOT wrap or shadow `Softellect.Sys.Errors`; it is the sole error channel for this part and is returned, never thrown.

### R-2. §I.2 [Core] — Published JSON Schema and validate-on-load

`OpticalConstructor.Storage.fsproj` MUST ship the file `schema/optical-constructor-project.schema.json` as a build-copied content item, carrying `"$id": "https://berreman/schema/optical-constructor-project.json"` and the `$defs` enumerated in §A.7 (`opticalSystem`, `layer`, `opticalProperties`, `beamNode`, `beamBranch`, `constructorElement`, `materialEntry`, `sourceSpec`, `unitOfMeasure`). This part authors the schema's **top-level envelope and the storage-owned `$defs`** (`materialEntry`, `sourceSpec`, `unitOfMeasure`, and the project root object: `schemaVersion` string, `systems`, `materials`, `sources`, `sweeps`, `chartSettings`, `beamTree`, plus optional `sidecars` array); the physics-shaped `$defs` (`opticalSystem`, `layer`, `opticalProperties`, `beamNode`, `beamBranch`, `constructorElement`) are filled by Parts B–G and MUST NOT be re-shaped here.

`deserializeProject` (I.1) MUST validate the parsed JSON document against this schema **before** binding it to `OpticalConstructorProject`, using **JsonSchema.Net** (the package Part A admits) — load the schema once into a `JsonSchema` value and call `Evaluate`. On any validation failure the function MUST return `SchemaValidationError` carrying the list of JsonSchema.Net evaluation messages and MUST NOT return a partially-bound project. If the schema content item is absent at runtime the function MUST return `SchemaMissing`. Schema **versioning and migration are out of scope**: a `schemaVersion` whose value does not equal the single shipped version MUST surface as `SchemaValidationError`, not trigger any migration code.

### R-3. §I.3 [Core] — Project file read/write with `.ocproj` extension

`OpticalConstructor.Storage.fsproj` MUST provide `ProjectFile` with `saveProject : string -> OpticalConstructorProject -> Result<unit, StorageError>` and `openProject : string -> Result<OpticalConstructorProject, StorageError>`. `saveProject` MUST serialize via `serializeProject` (I.1) and write the resulting UTF-8 text to the given path with the extension `.ocproj`; `openProject` MUST read the file, then call `deserializeProject` (I.2) so that schema validation always runs on load. All filesystem access MUST be wrapped so any exception becomes `FileIoError`; exceptions MUST NOT propagate out of these functions (project CLAUDE.md, `Result`-not-exceptions).

The canonical project is a single self-contained JSON text file — it MUST NOT be a zip, a folder bundle, or a multi-file container. Sidecars (I.4) live beside it as separate `.binz` files referenced by relative path from the JSON's `sidecars` array. `.ocproj` files are user documents and MUST NOT be added to any `.gitignore`; autosave and sidecar artefacts are addressed in I.5 and I.4 respectively. This `openProject` path is the single project-open seam every other part routes template loads and gallery loads through (Part J §J.3, §J.11).

### R-4. §I.4 [Core/Standard] — `.binz` sidecars for derived/bulk artefacts only

`OpticalConstructor.Storage.fsproj` MUST provide `Sidecar` with `writeSidecar<'T> : string -> 'T -> Result<unit, StorageError>` and `readSidecar<'T> : string -> Result<'T, StorageError>`, used **only** for derived/bulk artefacts: parametric-sweep result tables (the output of `calculate`/`calculate3D`, `Variables.fs:237,270` per Part A), in-layer field maps, and fit/design histories. These functions MUST reuse `Softellect.Sys.Core.serialize`/`deserialize` with `BinaryZippedFormat` (`C:/GitHub/Softellect/Sys/Core.fs:254,257`), and the file extension MUST be `.binz` (`Softellect.Sys.Primitives.fs:267`). Reuse is mandatory: do NOT introduce a second pickler, a second zip path, or a custom binary format — the one primitive to reach for is `Softellect.Sys.Core.serialize BinaryZippedFormat`.

`.binz` sidecars MUST NOT carry the canonical project definition or any hand/LLM-editable content (binding rule 4); attempting to serialize `OpticalConstructorProject` through `writeSidecar` is forbidden by directive and MUST NOT be done. Each sidecar is referenced from the project JSON only by **relative path** under the `sidecars` array (I.2); the schema MUST require those paths to be relative so a moved project folder keeps its sidecars. Sidecars are regenerable derived data and SHOULD be excluded from version control: this part's `files` list contributes a `.gitignore` entry for `*.binz` under the project working folder. Caching policies, sidecar eviction, and retention windows are OUT OF SCOPE.

## Non-requirements

- No recent-files list, autosave, undo/redo (`EditHistory`), CSV/Excel export, report generation, material-library import/export, or design-history — those are Part I §I.5–§I.8, owned by slice 013 (and the material import/export CSV path is slice 004).
- No schema versioning or migration code — a mismatched `schemaVersion` surfaces as `SchemaValidationError`, never a migration (OUT OF SCOPE per §I.2 / binding rule 6).
- No `*.autosave` `.gitignore` entry here — that is added by slice 013 (§I.5). This slice contributes only the `*.binz` entry per §I.4.
- The physics `$defs` (`opticalSystem`, `layer`, `opticalProperties`, `beamNode`, `beamBranch`, `constructorElement`) are filled by Parts B–G; this slice authors only the top-level envelope and the storage-owned `$defs` (`materialEntry`, `sourceSpec`, `unitOfMeasure`, project root) per §I.2.
- No second pickler, second zip path, or custom binary format; no caching/eviction/retention (§I.4 scope exclusion).
- No UI surfaces; no File ▸ Recent menu (that renders the slice-013 recent list).

