## Testing plan

- `build` gate: `dotnet build Berreman.slnx -c Release` from `Berreman/` MUST pass with the new storage modules and the schema content item compiling/copying in one pass.
- `unit-tests` gate: `dotnet test --no-build -c Release` from `Berreman/BerremanTests/` stays green (this slice does not touch `BerremanTests`).
- `constructor-unit-tests` gate runs the new `OpticalConstructor.Tests` files and MUST increase the count over slice 002's baseline. All `OpticalConstructor.*` tests are hosted in `OpticalConstructor.Tests` (no separate `OpticalConstructor.StorageTests` project — reconciler round-2 §g):
  - `ProjectJsonRoundtripTests.fs` — beam tree round-trips through the JSON-canonical project, validates against schema, default-unit hook preserved, no `.binz` write, SI values unchanged (AC-A2/AC-A5/AC-D6).
  - `RoundTripTests.fs` — `saveProject`→`openProject` identity over a representative `OpticalConstructorProject` (AC-I1); schema-violation returns `SchemaValidationError` (AC-I2); wrong `schemaVersion` rejected without migration (AC-I3).
  - `SidecarTests.fs` — `.binz` write/read identity for a sweep table; missing sidecar surfaces `SidecarMissing`/`BinzError` (AC-A6/AC-I4/AC-I5).

## Risks

- **Medium.** Storage is the early seam every later part serializes through; a wrong envelope or `$defs` shape forces re-validation downstream. The load-bearing worries are (a) the FSharp.SystemTextJson `JsonFSharpOptions` configuration round-tripping every DU/`option` idiomatically without storing a non-SI magnitude, (b) JsonSchema.Net `Evaluate` returning the message list verbatim into `SchemaValidationError`, and (c) keeping `OpticalConstructorProject` strictly off the `.binz` path (binding rule 4). Mitigation: prove round-trip identity, schema rejection, version mismatch, and sidecar miss by unit test before exit; keep the storage-owned `$defs` envelope minimal so Parts B–G can fill the physics `$defs` without re-shaping.

## Hand-off

Storage core exists and is unit-tested: canonical JSON serialize/deserialize (`ProjectJson.fs`), the published schema + validate-on-load (`SchemaValidation.fs`, `optical-constructor-project.schema.json`), `.ocproj` read/write (`ProjectFile.fs` — the single project-open seam), `.binz` sidecars for derived artefacts only (`Sidecar.fs`), and `StorageError` (`Errors.fs`) as the sole error channel. Later slices extend the aggregate and schema, not the reflection-based serializer: slice 004 adds the `materialEntry` dispersion sub-object, slice 007 sources, slice 012 chart settings; slice 013 adds recent files/autosave/undo-redo/export/report/material-import-export and the `*.autosave` `.gitignore` entry. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
